headline: 1 S&P 500 Stock to Own for Decades and 2 That Underwhelm
summary: While the S&P 500 (^GSPC) includes industry leaders, not every stock in the index is a winner. Some companies are past their prime, weighed down by poor execution, weak financials, or structural headwinds.

headline: Huntington Ingalls Supplies Virginia-Class Submarine to US Navy
summary: HII supplies the Virginia-class submarine Massachusetts to the U.S. Navy, underscoring its role as a key builder of advanced nuclear-powered vessels.

headline: Curtiss-Wright Boosts Share Buyback Authorization to $550 Million
summary: CW lifts its buyback authorization to $550 million, setting up record 2025 repurchases as strong cash flow fuels its shareholder-return strategy.

headline: Is General Dynamics Stock Outperforming the Nasdaq?
summary: While General Dynamics has surged past the Nasdaq Composite in 2025, it has slightly lagged behind the index recently. Analysts are cautiously optimistic about the stock’s growth potential.
